description._content: Title: Jamsetji Bend, Khandalla Creator: William Johnson Date: ca. 1855-1862 Part Of: Photographs of Western India Place: Khandala, Maharashtra, India Description: Causeway in Khandala, India, which is part of a system used to provide water for conversion to electrical power. Indian industrialist Jamsetji Tata was instrumental in developing the hydroelectric power project which first delivered inexpensive electrical power to Bombay (now Mumbai) in the early 20th century.
